Written by Viet Trung Tran (ENS Cachan)

Introduction
============

Gfarm2fs: file system interface for Gfarm/BlobSeer


Advanced Features
=================
Supported versioning capability. User can access file versions via ioctl commands:

ioctl(fd, BLOB_GET_LATEST_VERSION, &nversion);

ioctl(fd, BLOB_SET_ACTIVE_VERSION, &nversion);

ioctl(fd, BLOB_GET_ACTIVE_VERSION, &nversion);

Examples
========

#include "gfioctl.h" //ioctl supported

fd = open(argv[1], 0_RDWR);

np = pwrite(fd, buffer_w, BUFFER_SIZE,0);
ioctl(fd, BLOB_GET_LATEST_VERSION, &nversion);

ioctl(fd, BLOB_SET_ACTIVE_VERSION, &nversion);
np = pread(fd, buffer_r, BUFFER_SIZE,0);

ioctl(fd, BLOB_GET_ACTIVE_VERSION, &nversion);
close(fd);

Warning
=======
Build Gfarm2fs under linux kernel 2.6.29 or later. Otherwise, there is no versioning support.

Install
=======

CPPFLAGS='-I/usr/local/include -I$(Gfarm_includes) -I$(BlobSeer_includes)' LDFLAGS='-L/usr/local/lib -L$(Gfarm_libs) -L$(BlobSeer_libs) ' ./configure --prefix=$(Install_dir)

User's guide
============
+ mount the file system
	gfarm2fs $(destination_dir)
+ umount the file system
	sudo umount $(destination_dir)











